description:
Heroes for Hire Volume 3

Marvel's cosmic gurus Dan Abnett and Andy Lanning takes us to the streets of Marvel in this new series. Showcasing many of the former Marvel Knights in the grand tradition of Heroes For Hire, each hero or heroine must be ready when that call comes. "Hero, are you for hire tonight?"

The series lasted for 12 issues after which it continued in a one-shot named Spider-Island: Heroes For Hire and after that it was continued in Villains for Hire.

Collected Editions

  • Heroes for Hire: Control (#1-5)
  • Fear Itself: Heroes for Hire (#6-12)
name: Heroes for Hire

description: In the future, two warring cities continue to inflict pain and suffering upon their desperate citizens. Life is bleak and people have become apathetic to the situation: at home with the chaos. Then the appearance of several powerful strangers changes everything, and hot on their trail is a man known as Jake Thrash, a mysterious figure roaming the streets with a definite mission of his own. His connection to the strangers is unknown, but he will stop at nothing to end their terror in this three-issue mini-series with a Blade Runner feel to it.
name: Jake Thrash
